703796f-a.title: Brooklyn: Conklin Avenue - 95th Street (East)
703796f-a.text:
131-145 Conklin Ave., at the N.E. corner of East 95th Street. Part-
ially shown on the left, are Nos. 123-125 East 95th Street. I1 the cen-
ter of the view, is the former Canarsie Hotel; operated by Hy Lehman;
1873-1883. This building was stdccoed in 1925. I the foreground, is

703798f-a.title: Brooklyn: Conklin Avenue - 95th Street (East)
703798f-a.text:
Conklin Ave., east from East 95th Street, showing at left foreground,
the former Lehman Hotel, once frame, but now stuccoed. Across the street
was Lehman's general store.
April 1929.

703797f-a.title: Brooklyn: Conklin Avenue - 95th Street (East)
703797f-a.text:
132 Conklin Ave., at the S.E. corner of East 95th Street, sho ing C.6.
Lehman's general store; which was owned by one C.C. Quaritins in 1873. The
narrow part of the building faces Conklin Ave. The building at the right,

1922.
